<h1 id="lab-creating-a-streamlit-example-dashboard">Lab: Creating a
Streamlit Example Dashboard</h1>
<h2 id="objectives">Objectives</h2>
<ul>
<li>Understand how to build a dashboard using Streamlit.</li>
<li>Learn to create interactive UI components for data exploration.</li>
<li>Develop a sample dashboard to visualize and analyze data.</li>
<li>Deploy and run the Streamlit dashboard locally.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="lab-outline">Lab Outline</h2>
<h3 id="step-1-introduction-to-streamlit-dashboards">Step 1:
Introduction to Streamlit Dashboards</h3>
<ul>
<li>Overview of dashboards and Streamlit’s capabilities.</li>
<li>Installation instructions.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="step-2-setting-up-the-project">Step 2: Setting Up the
Project</h3>
<ul>
<li>Create a new project directory.</li>
<li>Set up a virtual environment.</li>
<li>Install Streamlit and required dependencies.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="step-3-building-the-example-dashboard">Step 3: Building the
Example Dashboard</h3>
<ul>
<li>Create a basic Streamlit dashboard (<code>dashboard.py</code>).</li>
<li>Add UI elements: dashboard title, description, and sidebar
filters.</li>
<li>Load and display a sample dataset (e.g., CSV file).</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="step-4-adding-interactivity">Step 4: Adding Interactivity</h3>
<ul>
<li>Use widgets (e.g., sliders, select boxes, checkboxes) for user
input.</li>
<li>Filter and update data visualizations based on user selections.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="step-5-visualizing-data">Step 5: Visualizing Data</h3>
<ul>
<li>Integrate charts (e.g., line chart, bar chart, pie chart) using
Streamlit’s built-in functions.</li>
<li>Display summary statistics and dynamic outputs.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="step-6-running-and-testing-the-dashboard">Step 6: Running and
Testing the Dashboard</h3>
<ul>
<li>Launch the Streamlit dashboard locally.</li>
<li>Test all interactive features and data visualizations.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="step-7-summary-and-next-steps">Step 7: Summary and Next
Steps</h3>
<ul>
<li>Review key concepts learned.</li>
<li>Suggestions for enhancing the dashboard (e.g., adding more charts,
using real datasets).</li>
</ul>
